title._content: Photographic postcard of a swimming champion, possibly 'M. Kershaw'

description._content: A postcard featuring a black and white photograph of a man in a swimming costume, with several badges pinned to his chest. He has his hand resting on a table containing three trophies. The front has been signed with his name, which is illegible. On the back of the postcard is a letter to Miss Beatrice Kerr. If reproduced or distributed, this image should be clearly attributed to the collection of the Australian National Maritime Museum; and not be used for any commercial or for-profit purposes without the permission of the museum. For more information see our Flickr Commons Rights Statement. The ANMM undertakes research and accepts public comments that enhance the information we hold about images in our collection. This record has been updated accordingly. If you can identify a person, vessel or landmark, write the details in the Comments box below. Thank you for helping caption this important historical image. Object number ANMS1032[026]
